**🗄️ DATABASE ARCHITECTURE & SECURITY**

**Database Schema Design**
```
Core Database Structure:

┌─────────────────┐ ┌──────────────────┐ ┌─────────────────┐
│   Cases Table   │ │  Evidence Table  │ │  Users Table    │
├─────────────────┤ ├──────────────────┤ ├─────────────────┤
│ case_id (PK)    │ │ evidence_id (PK) │ │ user_id (PK)    │
│ case_number     │ │ case_id (FK)     │ │ username        │
│ case_type       │ │ evidence_type    │ │ password_hash   │
│ case_date       │ │ file_path        │ │ role            │
│ status          │ │ file_hash        │ │ permissions     │
│ created_by      │ │ chain_of_custody │ │ last_login      │
│ created_date    │ │ created_by       │ │ account_status  │
│ modified_date   │ │ created_date     │ │ two_factor_auth │
└─────────────────┘ └──────────────────┘ └─────────────────┘

┌─────────────────┐ ┌──────────────────┐ ┌─────────────────┐
│   Transactions  │ │  Sessions Table  │ │  Audit Log      │
├─────────────────┤ ├──────────────────┤ ├─────────────────┤
│ transaction_id  │ │ session_id       │ │ log_id          │
│ evidence_id     │ │ user_id (FK)     │ │ user_id (FK)    │
│ action_type     │ │ session_start    │ │ action_type     │
│ timestamp       │ │ session_end      │ │ timestamp       │
│ user_id         │ │ ip_address       │ │ details         │
│ details         │ │ device_info      │ │ ip_address      │
│ data_before     │ └──────────────────┘ └─────────────────┘
│ data_after      └──────────────────┘ └─────────────────┘
```

**Security Implementation**

**1. Authentication System**
```csharp
// Multi-factor authentication structure
public class SecurityManager {
    // Password security
    public string HashPassword(string password) {
        // PBKDF2 with salt
        using (var pbkdf2 = new Rfc2898DeriveBytes(password, salt, 10000)) {
            return Convert.ToBase64String(pbkdf2.GetBytes(32));
        }
    }
    
    // Two-factor authentication
    public bool Validate2FA(string code, string userId) {
        // SMS-based or authenticator app
        // Valid for 30 seconds
        // Rate limiting: max 3 attempts per 5 minutes
    }
    
    // Session management
    public string CreateSecureSession(User user) {
        // JWT token with 15-minute expiry
        // Refresh tokens with 7-day expiry
        // IP-based session validation
    }
}
```

**2. Data Encryption Strategy**
```
Encryption Layers:

🔹 Application Layer:
• Input validation and sanitization
• SQL injection prevention
• XSS protection
• CSRF token validation

🔹 Transport Layer:
• HTTPS/TLS 1.3 for all connections
• Certificate pinning
• Perfect Forward Secrecy

🔹 Database Layer:
• AES-256 encryption for sensitive data
• Transparent Data Encryption (TDE)
• Column-level encryption for PII

🔹 File Storage Layer:
• Encrypted file system
• Hash-based file verification
• Secure backup protocols
```

**3. Database Security Measures**
```
Database Security Framework:

🛡️ Access Control:
├── Role-based permissions (RBAC)
├── Principle of least privilege
├── Multi-factor admin access
├── IP whitelisting for admins

🔒 Data Protection:
├── Encryption at rest (AES-256)
├── Encryption in transit (TLS 1.3)
├── Data masking for sensitive fields
├── Secure backup with encryption

🔍 Monitoring & Auditing:
├── Real-time security monitoring
├── Automated threat detection
├── Comprehensive audit logging
├── Intrusion detection systems

📊 Compliance Features:
├── Evidence integrity verification
├── Chain of custody tracking
├── Legal compliance reporting
└── Privacy protection features
```

